# Filenames / paths blocked from being committed by the global pre-commit hook.
# One POSIX extended regex per line, matched against staged file paths
# (the output of `git diff --cached --name-only`). Lines starting with # ignored.
#
# When a staged path matches any pattern, the commit is blocked with a list of
# offending files and instructions to:
#   1. KEEP IT BLOCKED — do nothing.
#   2. UNTRACK IT — `git rm --cached <file>` (if it was tracked before),
#      then re-stage the rest, commit again.
#   3. ACCEPT IT — bypass this one commit with `git commit --no-verify`.
#
# This file is a belt-and-suspenders companion to ~/.gitignore_global. The
# global gitignore handles the silent case; this hook handles AIs that try
# `git add -f` or commit files that were already tracked.

# ---- AI assistant files (never committed) ----
(^|/)CLAUDE\.md$
(^|/)\.claude(/|$)
(^|/)AGENTS\.md$
(^|/)GEMINI\.md$
(^|/)GEMINI(/|$)

# ---- Personal working notes & local-only vaults (never committed) ----
(^|/)docs(/|$)
(^|/)private(/|$)

# ---- Add more patterns as you discover AI mistakes ----
